email: mshio@ka2.so-net.ne.jp
[These are fascinating observations and might very well explain a great
deal. Sequencing of EV-71 virus isolates will provide additional useful
information regarding differences between the currently circulating
isolates and reference strains. Whether or not EV 71 is eventually
confirmed as the single etiologic agent of the complex cases in these
epidemics, it should be emphasized that clinical symptoms caused by
simultaneously superimposed virus infections are not described in
textbooks. - Mod.CHC
[When considering these results, bear in mind the following:
1) In the first case, a brain stem lesion was suspected but never actually
seen.
2) In the last case, a brain stem lesion was seen, but EV-71 was never
actually isolated.
3) EV-71 is said to be more difficult to isolate than other enteroviruses,
yet more EV-71 isolates have been reported than other viruses. However, we
have reason to believe that more viruses have been isolated than have been
reported, including one or more possibly new coltiviruses. - Mod.JW
...........................................chc/jw/es
